### impl&lt;T, U&gt; [Into](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/convert/trait.Into.html) &lt;U&gt; for T where U: [From](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/convert/trait.From.html) &lt;T&gt;, [§](#method.into)
#### fn [into](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/convert/trait.Into.html) (self) -&gt; U
Calls `U::from(self)`.

That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of `From&lt;T&gt; for U` chooses to do. [Source](https://docs.rs/tower/0.5.2/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/src/tower/make/make_service.rs.html) [§](#impl-MakeService%3CTarget,+Request%3E-for-M)
