#### fn [boxed](https://docs.rs/tower/0.5.2/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower/util/trait.ServiceExt.html) (self) -&gt; [BoxService](https://docs.rs/tower/0.5.2/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower/util/boxed/sync/struct.BoxService.html) &lt;Request, Self:: [Response](https://docs.rs/tower-service/0.3.3/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_service/trait.Service.html), Self:: [Error](https://docs.rs/tower-service/0.3.3/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_service/trait.Service.html) &gt; where Self: [Sized](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/marker/trait.Sized.html) + [Send](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/marker/trait.Send.html) + 'static, Self:: [Future](https://docs.rs/tower-service/0.3.3/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_service/trait.Service.html): [Send](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/marker/trait.Send.html) + 'static, Convert the service into a [`Service`](https://docs.rs/tower-service/0.3.3/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_service/trait.Service.html) + [`Send`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/marker/trait.Send.html) trait object. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower/0.5.2/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower/util/trait.ServiceExt.html) Convert the service into a [`Service`](https://docs.rs/tower-service/0.3.3/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_service/trait.Service.html) + [`Clone`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/clone/trait.Clone.html) + [`Send`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/marker/trait.Send.html) trait object. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower/0.5.2/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower/util/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `propagate-header`** only. Propagate a header from the request to the response. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) [Source](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/src/tower_http/service_ext.rs.html) [§](#method.add_extension)
#### fn [add_extension](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) &lt;T&gt;(self, value: T) -&gt; [AddExtension](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/add_extension/struct.AddExtension.html) &lt;Self, T&gt; where Self: [Sized](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/core/marker/trait.Sized.html), Available on **crate feature `add-extension`** only. Available on **crate feature `map-request-body`** only. Apply a transformation to the request body. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `map-response-body`** only. Apply a transformation to the response body. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate features `compression-br` or `compression-deflate` or `compression-gzip` or `compression-zstd`** only. Compresses response bodies. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate features `decompression-br` or `decompression-deflate` or `decompression-gzip` or `decompression-zstd`** only. Decompress response bodies. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `trace`** only. High level tracing that classifies responses using HTTP status codes. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `trace`** only. High level tracing that classifies responses using gRPC headers. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `follow-redirect`** only. Follow redirect resposes using the [`Standard`](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/follow_redirect/policy/type.Standard.html) policy. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `sensitive-headers`** only. Mark headers as [sensitive](https://docs.rs/http/latest/http/header/struct.HeaderValue.html) on both requests and responses. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `sensitive-headers`** only. Mark headers as [sensitive](https://docs.rs/http/latest/http/header/struct.HeaderValue.html) on requests. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `sensitive-headers`** only. Mark headers as [sensitive](https://docs.rs/http/latest/http/header/struct.HeaderValue.html) on responses. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `set-header`** only. Insert a header into the request. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `set-header`** only. Append a header into the request. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `set-header`** only. Insert a header into the request, if the header is not already present. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `set-header`** only. Insert a header into the response. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `set-header`** only. Append a header into the response. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `set-header`** only. Insert a header into the response, if the header is not already present. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) [Source](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/src/tower_http/service_ext.rs.html) [§](#method.set_request_id)
#### fn [set_request_id](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) &lt;M&gt;(self, header_name: [HeaderName](https://docs.rs/http/1.3.1/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/http/header/name/struct.HeaderName.html), make_request_id: M,) -&gt; [SetRequestId](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/request_id/struct.SetRequestId.html) &lt;Self, M&gt; Available on **crate feature `request-id`** only. Add request id header and extension. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) [Source](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/src/tower_http/service_ext.rs.html) [§](#method.set_x_request_id)
#### fn [set_x_request_id](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) &lt;M&gt;(self, make_request_id: M) -&gt; [SetRequestId](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/request_id/struct.SetRequestId.html) &lt;Self, M&gt; Available on **crate feature `request-id`** only. Add request id header and extension, using `x-request-id` as the header name. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `request-id`** only. Propgate request ids from requests to responses. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `request-id`** only. Propgate request ids from requests to responses, using `x-request-id` as the header name. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `catch-panic`** only. Catch panics and convert them into `500 Internal Server` responses. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `limit`** only. Intercept requests with over-sized payloads and convert them into `413 Payload Too Large` responses. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `normalize-path`** only. Remove trailing slashes from paths. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) Available on **crate feature `normalize-path`** only. Append trailing slash to paths. [Read more](https://docs.rs/tower-http/0.6.6/x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/tower_http/service_ext/trait.ServiceExt.html) [§](#impl-ToOwned-for-T)
